Let’s be real: babies are blobs. They don’t do much but sleep, poop, and cry. As they start to move and become more interactive, then it’s a different story.

I was in no rush to travel when Elliot was a baby. It just seemed like I was dragging another piece of luggage around.

But now that he’s a toddler, I’m excited to travel again! He listens, interacts with things, and is excited about everything we show him. He absorbs it all like a sponge, and it’s magical to watch.

I’m finally ready to travel with him, because I think he’s ready!

#travelwithkids #toddlers #familytravel

Don’t do it girl, you are going to miss that connection.

⚠️ A 10-minute delay can be enough to make you miss your connecting flight. Because boarding closes usually 15 minutes before scheduled departure (30 minutes for international flights), you actually only have 10-25 minutes to disembark, get to the next gate, and board. This doesn’t account for changing carriers or going international, which may require you to walk or take transit to a different terminal.

✅ TLDR: it’s not as much time as you think to catch your connecting flight!

Sometime that extra savings isn’t worth the stress and change of missing your next flight.

#travelmistakes #travelmishaps #rookietravel

Happy Belated Mother’s Day! 💐 Two of the biggest things I've struggled with since becoming a mother have been time management and being present. 

Tasks now take longer: getting out the door, eating, traveling, filming, and editing. We can’t work crazy hours to meet tight deadlines anymore, and we can’t produce content as quickly as we did before because there are simply fewer hours in the day available for us to work.

Being present and in the moment when engaging with Elliot is another challenge. I realize I have a slight phone addiction, as most of us do, but really dedicating time to be 100% there, setting aside blocks of time each day to play, talk, and share these special moments, is what being a parent is all about. It’s why we chose this, to share our lives with these little people, to watch them grow, to help them learn, and to give and receive love.

And oh boy, do I love this little guy more than anything, and his love in return is the best part of being a mother. 💕

[SAVE & SHARE] Tips for Visiting 📍Maho Beach with children.

✅ I initially thought it would be too loud, but most of the planes are smaller and not significantly louder than everyday noise. The larger planes do make more noise, especially when they arrive in the afternoon. For those ones we covered Elliot’s ears and we stood away from them on the sides of the beach!

✅ Stay to the sides! You can watch the airplanes land without getting any of the backdraft or sand blasts. We rented two beach chairs for $20 USD for the day, right by the bar. Although it’s not the nicest area, it’s quieter and you can still see all the same planes. Our toddler wasn’t fazed by the noise at all.

✅ The beach isn’t great for swimming due to a large drop-off, and unexpected waves caused by larger planes. As a result, we didn’t spend a lot of time in the water and mostly played in the sand instead.

✅ There’s a schedule posted at the bar of all the larger planes landing. You can also check the Princess Juliana International Airport website for a list of departures and landings.

✅ Planes taking off are the loudest and most dangerous. They produce the jet blasts that can hurt & knock people over. For the couple we saw, we simply covered Elliot’s ears & stayed very far away (by the bar area) and it was fine. Planes landing are much quieter than those taking off.

✅ There is a bar area for food and drinks, and plenty of shuttles and taxis to take you there and back whenever you need. You can also just watch the planes from there no problem.

✅ Go for the spectacle, not for the beach. There are plenty of better beaches to take kids to, so unless they love airplanes, I would go somewhere else instead. But if they do enjoy watching airplanes and you happen to be in Sint Maarten, this is one stop you cannot miss!

If you are looking for alternative things to do in Sint Maarten, check out @Expedia ‘s Things to Do section, full of organized tours you can easily book and add onto your time there!

#EGPartner

Here’s some tips for visiting: 👇

📍Magens Bay Beach, St. Thomas USVI 

✅ It’s a large beach: Despite being there with two large cruise ships, the beach was spacious enough for everyone. If you want an emptier spot, or some shade, simply walk further down the beach.

✅ Rent a beach chair and umbrella: While they’re in a prime location near the bus drop-off area, food, and washrooms, they are a bit pricey at $20 USD per chair. But if you want convenience and shade, it’s worth it.

✅ Pack a picnic before visiting the beach bar: We packed plenty of snacks for Elliot and were glad we did because food options at Magens Bay are limited. For a few slices of pizza, Matt waited in line for over 30 minutes.

✅ Use reef-safe sunscreen: Not only is it legally required, but we should all try to protect the delicate marine ecosystem by choosing reef-safe sunscreen. These sunscreens are free from harmful chemicals that can damage coral reefs and marine life.

✅ Visit the nearby nature trail: If you need a break from the sun, take a stroll along the Magens Bay nature trail. This short hike offers a glimpse of the lush St. Thomas flora and fauna and a spectacular view of the bay. We didn’t have a chance to do it, but it would have been a great option if the weather wasn’t as good.

✅ Plan transportation in advance: Magens Bay is about a 30-minute drive from the cruise ship port or downtown Charlotte Amalie. We talked to our van driver to arrange transportation back, but even then, all the drivers fill up their cars as quickly as possible. Note that there are plenty of shuttles available to take you back, but most are open seating, which wasn’t suitable for us with a toddler. So, we made sure to wait for a closed van.

If you are looking for alternative things to do in St Thomas, check out @Expedia “Things To Do” section, full of organized tours you can easily book and add onto your time there!

More of my Top Things to Do in 📍Singapore 👇

✅ Marina Bay Sands: This iconic Singaporean landmark is a must-see. You can enjoy the infinity pool, visit the SkyPark Observation Deck, or shop in its luxury mall.

✅ Singapore Zoo Night Safari: It’s the world’s first nocturnal zoo. Take a tram ride or walk the trails to see animals in their night-time environments.

✅ Orchard Road: Known as the shopping hub of Singapore, Orchard Road is a must-visit for shopping enthusiasts. Here, you can find everything from high-end fashion brands to budget-friendly options.

✅ Clarke Quay: This riverside quay is known for its exciting nightlife, with numerous bars, restaurants, and nightclubs.

✅ Hawker Centers: Try local Singaporean food in one of the many hawker centers around the city.

✅National Museum of Singapore: Learn about Singapore’s history at the oldest museum in the city, known for its innovative exhibitions.

✅Singapore Botanic Gardens: Visit this UNESCO World Heritage site, a beautiful tropical garden, perfect for nature lovers and those who enjoy peaceful walks.

✅ Singapore Jewel Waterfall-Before you fly home, visit the world’s tallest indoor waterfall at the Changi Airport.

Discovery more in @Expedia ‘s Things To Do section, full of organized tours & early bird tickets you can easily purchase for your trip!

Let’s get you caught up…  where shall we go from here?

How many have YOU done? 👀👇

🧗‍♀️Adrenaline Rush- You are young and your body is in peak condition, perfect for high adrenaline activities! There are dozens of places around the world perfect for getting your blood pumping. 

🇪🇺Euro-Trip -What’s more iconic than the Euro-Trip!? Visiting multiple countries and iconic hot spots in one great, epic trip to Europe.

🥾Multi-Day Hiking Trip- You don’t need to go far to have this experience. Hiking for multiple days, pushing yourself physically, and camping are very rewarding travel experiences. Check around locally to see what trips you can take nearby.

🚗North American Road Trip- North America is full of National Parks to explore. It can also be cheaper to drive around North America, as opposed to flying.

🐘Thailand- It’s cheap, exotic and easy to get around. Thailand is perfect for all types of travel. You have culture, beachy islands, great food and plenty of info to help you navigate.

🎒South East Asia Backpacking- The perfect beginner backpacking trip for those looking for a cheap, exotic and not too difficult to navigate trip.

🚤Boating Trip- Nothing beats getting out onto the ocean, whether for just a few hours, a day or more, or taking part in a yacht week. Any kind of boat will do, just get out there!

🤿Learn to Scuba - Tired of sights above the land? Head on down under the sea to experience a whole new world. Learning to scuba usually takes 3-4 days, but it’s totally unlike anything else you’ve ever done.

🇬🇷Greek Island Hopping- Each of the Greek islands are so different that hopping between them make for a great, varied trip. Beaches, parties, sunsets, volcanos, ruins – they have them all.

🦎Jungle Adventure- This doesn’t have to be the Amazon, but experiencing the wet and wild jungle is a unique adventure. Just plan your seasons accordingly, as the wet or dry season means these destinations will vary quite a lot.

What have been some of YOUR most memorable trips in your 20s?

Which one are YOU most excited about doing 👀👇

💁‍♀️Solo Trip- Doesn’t have to be long or far, just go somewhere or do something on your own.

🎿Ski Trip- Travel doesn’t stop just because it’s winter. Europe and North America are full of amazing ski resorts. Head up the slope for some winter fun. If you go in December, you can experience the Christmas Markets.

⛩️Cultural Shock- Go somewhere so completely different than what you are used to, to experience a true surprise. 

🎰Casino Trip- Vegas or Monaco, these destinations are wild, fun and you’ll probably lose some money... but that’s part of the experience!

👙Spring Break- Cancun probably comes to mind here, but you can go anywhere sunny. Beaches, partying, swimming, it’s the perfect time to let loose and have a bit of fun between school or work.

🌆Big City- New York, London, Tokyo, Seoul, Paris, Hong Kong, if you’ve never experienced a big city before, now is your time.

🎡Festivals - These are a must for your 20’s, experiencing the fun of festival life. There’s music, art, beer, folk, any type of festival you can imagine!

🏄‍♀️Surf Trip- Australia, South Africa, New Zealand, Hawaii, Bali, Costa Rica, catch a wave and spend some time surfing the ocean and experiencing surf culture.

📖Work/Study Abroad- Most study abroad programs are open to under 30’s so take advantage of the easier Visa requirements to live, work or study in another country. 

👯‍♀️Friends Trip- Girls, guys, couples whatever, go on a trip with your best group of friends!

How many have you done? What have been some of YOUR most memorable trips in your 20s?

Don’t worry 30 year olds, I got one coming for you!

 [SAVE & SHARE] Follow for part 1! 

@heynadine  for more travel inspiration & tips!

Which ones are YOU dreaming of taking? 😊👇

🎂Big 30 - Celebrate the new decade in style! Whether it’s going to a club, a wine tasting, or any other activity that appeals to you and your group of friends.

🍝Foodie Trip - You’re likely more comfortable in your body now and appreciate good food. So indulge and enjoy on a delicious trip full of great food!

🥂Luxury Trip - You’re probably more financially stable now than you were in your 20s. So treat yourself to that once-in-a-lifetime trip. 

🧘‍♀️Wellness Trip - You’ve most likely spent a good portion of your life hustling in the corporate/working world. Take a trip to unwind, relax, and rejuvenate your body and mind. 

🛳️Cruise - If you’re looking for a trip that accommodates multiple generations of family, a cruise is a great option. With multiple cruise lines catering to different cruising styles, there’s plenty of options and things to do for everyone.

🚐RV Camping Trip - If your body isn’t the same as it was in your 20s, renting a campervan, RV, or trailer is a comfortable, and enjoyable way to spend time in nature. Experience the great outdoors with the convenience of AC and heat.

🐅Safari - Even though you’re 30, not 50, an African safari isn’t just a trip for older people. Witnessing herds of animals in their natural habitat is an incredible experience at any age.

⚽️Event Trip - Use your disposable income to see that concert, show or big sports game/event you’ve always wanted to attend!

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦Family Trip - Since you may have more family members now, enjoy some quality time together at a beach or lake. Sometimes simplicity is best when traveling with kids.

🏖️All-Inclusive - Before dismissing them, consider the variety of all-inclusive resorts available today. There are luxury, adult-only options with entertainment and unlimited food.

Plus all 20 trips you could still take from your 20s! (see previous reels) Age is just a number and you’re not that old, yet 😜

I have a little secret to share with you... this isn’t the first time I’ve reached 100k followers on IG 🤫

I lost followers when I started posting silly short videos during my pregnancy.

I lost followers when we bought and then sold our Westfalia.

I lost followers when I got married, when I stopped traveling as much, and when I had Elliot.

This is the reality of this platform: as you change, your audience changes. As a creator, it’s disheartening to put so much work and effort into attracting an audience that cares, only to later realize they don’t anymore.

To witness those numbers decline and to wonder, “what am I doing wrong?”, “why don’t people like me anymore?”.

But the truth is, everyone’s life has seasons, just like with friendships. There is a period of time when my life aligns with your life, and I can provide you with the value you are seeking.

But then, as our priorities shift and we grow older, we naturally drift apart.

However, there are always people who are in that new season of life, currently aligned with your thoughts and values. And when they find you, they will resonate with your content and be grateful it exists. And they’ll follow, just like I do with the creators I currently watch.

This isn’t just applicable to creators; it holds true for all aspects of life. 

So I’m grateful for all those who have followed in the past, whom I’ve helped, and I’m not sad when they decide it’s time to go. Because I’m excited to help all the new people who have just started this journey with me, to share with them the new value I provide.

So if you are new to me, welcome! And if you’ve been here for a while, thank you! 💖

#creatorjourney #100kfollowers #100k #contentcreator
